<article id="post-337" class="post-337 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-trains category-travel tag-hiroshima tag-japan tag-kyoto tag-miyajima tag-shinkansen">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-kyoto/" rel="bookmark">Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Kyoto</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>We woke before 8:00 this morning, expecting breakfast. At least, that was the time they put on the reservation notice I got from the guest house reservation service. We didn&#8217;t eat until about 8:30, though, which was fine.<br />
Breakfast was mostly western: scrambled eggs, toast, orange juice, and the like. Nothing particularly fancy.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2004/03/turning-japanese-again-shinkansen-kyoto/#more-337" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Turning Japanese Again, Shinkansen to Kyoto&#8221;</span></a></p>
